   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Forty-nine RECONCILED TO GOD Scripture: Rom 5:1, 9-11 Man s conflict with God Since the time Adam sinned, man has had conflict and discord with God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>We have had conflict with God from the time of our birth.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>We are in conflict with God in all our daily living and walk.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Man as God s enemy We have not only received from Adam a life that has conflict with God, but also in this life we have Satan s nature and are enemies to God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>From the time of our birth, we are against God and are God s enemies.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Our human living is against God.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Reconciled to God God sent the Lord Jesus to take away our sins through the redemptive work of the cross, thus resolving the conflict between God and us.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God sent the Holy Spirit to move us and to cause us to repent and turn to Him.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Once we believe in the Lord Jesus, our sins are forgiven and we are justified, accepted, and reconciled to God.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>How to be reconciled to God</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
